REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='857', `RecipeID`='857', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Cook cake as directed let completely cool, Mix up jello as if you were going to eat it alone, poke LOTS of holes in cake, Pour jello really slowly to ensure it soaks into the cake place cake in the refrigerator for 2 hrs to let jello set up, once set up pull cake out of the fridge and top with whipped cream (as icing), My children and i like to put sliced fruit ontop for added color and decorations.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='858', `RecipeID`='858', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a medium bowl, whisk jello mix into water until blended. Fold in the cool whip. Pour into pie crust. Freeze at least one hour before serving (if frozen longer, thaw in fridge before serving). Easy, guilt-free and delicious! Kids love helping and eating this pie. I used';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='859', `RecipeID`='859', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat the oven to 325°F/165°C Grease a 10 bundt pan with butter or shortening very liberally. Dust the pan with flour and set aside. Place all the cake ingredients in the bowl of your stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment. Mix on low for 30 seconds and then increase the speed to medium and mix for 3 minutes. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 65-75 minutes until a toothpick entered into the center comes out clean. When the cake is done make the glaze. Combine all ingredients into a small saucepan over medium-low heat. Stir continuously until the butter is melted and the sugar is dissolved. Do not bring to a boil. Poke holes all over the warm cake using a knife and pour the glaze evenly on the cake while still in the pan. Allow the cake to cool completely in the pan and then invert the cake onto a serving plate. Dust with powdered sugar if you like. I actually like to make this cake a day in advance, finding it to be more moist and flavorful when it rests overnight.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='860', `RecipeID`='860', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1/2 cup butter, melted 1 cup sugar 1/2 cup flour 2 eggs, beaten 1 teaspoon vanilla 3/4 cup chocolate chips 3/4 cup pecans or 3/4 cup walnuts 9 inches unbaked pie shells';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='861', `RecipeID`='861', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix ingredients 1-4. Pour into crust. Bake for 12-14 minutes. Let cool completely. Top with whipped cream.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='862', `RecipeID`='862', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix all ingredients well. Crush approximately 1 cup of graham crackers and set aside on a plate. Mix the remaining ingredients until well blended together in a medium size bowl. Cover and chill in the refrigerator for about 15 minutes. Take mixture out of bowl,form into a ball and roll in the crushed graham crackers to coat. Cover with cellophane and return the cheese ball back to the refrigerator for an hour to chill or use right away if you prefer. Serve with cinnamon or honey graham crackers.';
