REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1061', `RecipeID`='1061', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Blend together all of the ingredients until smooth in a blender or food processor. 2 Spoon into a bowl, cover, and chill for at least three hours, or overnight. 3 Serve chilled, at room temperature, or even slightly heated.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1062', `RecipeID`='1062', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Fry bacon. Chop tomatos. Combine all ingredients in bowl. Eat with crackers, toast, or chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1063', `RecipeID`='1063', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Combine cream cheese, sour cream, and Ranch Dip mix and mix until smooth. Spread into the bottom of a 9-inch pie plate or other similarly sized pan. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, bacon, blue cheese, and chives. Serve with Chips and ENJOY!!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1064', `RecipeID`='1064', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Place all ingredients into a saucepan. 2 Bring to a boil, lower to simmer, cook for 15 minutes until slightly thick, stirring occasionally. 3 Let it cool slightly. 4 Pour into blender and puree. 5 Use as you would any bbq sauce, on chicken, pork, or tuna';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1065', `RecipeID`='1065', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Trim excess fat from beef. Heat oil in 10 skillet over medium heat. Cook beef for 10 minutes, turning frequently, to brown all sides. Place beef in 3-1/2 to 6-quart slow cooker. Pour remaining ingredients over beef. cover and cook on low heat setting for 8-10 hours, until beef is tender. Remove beef from crockpot and shred, using two forks. Skim fat from juices in crockpot, and add beef. Keep on low setting until ready to serve, and while serving too. Serves 10-12';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1066', `RecipeID`='1066', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain thoroughly. Add remaining ingredients except Ranch-Style dressing; mix well. Add 1/2 of Ranch-Style dressing; taste, and add more if needed.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1067', `RecipeID`='1067', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Melt cheese with soup. Stir constantly and add broccoli. Heat thoroughly. Serve with veggiesor chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1068', `RecipeID`='1068', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Lightly coat an 8×8 baking dish with nonstick spray. Heat olive oil in a medium skillet over medium high heat. Season chicken breast with salt and pepper, to taste. Add to skillet and cook, flipping once, until cooked through, about 3-4 minutes per side. Let cool before shredding and combining with Frank’s RedHot; set aside. Reheat re fried beans according to package instructions. Spread the re fried beans in an even layer into the prepared baking dish. Without stirring, top with PHILADELPHIA Cream Cheese. Spread the chicken mixture on top in an even layer and sprinkle with cheese. Place into oven and bake until bubbly, about 15-18 minutes. Serve immediately, drizzled with sour cream and garnished with avocado and cilantro, if desired.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1069', `RecipeID`='1069', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Combine all ingredients in microwave safe bowl. Stir. Place in microwave on high for 5 minutes or until cream cheese has melted. Stirring occasionally.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1070', `RecipeID`='1070', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a large bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, sour cream, chives, parsley, dill, garlic powder, onion powder, salt and pepper.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1071', `RecipeID`='1071', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a skillet over medium heat, melt butter and olive oil together. Add in flour, stirring constantly until smooth. Lower heat and stir in cream, whisking continuously. Remove from heat and add in spices, stirring until thickened. Then stir in the cheese until melted, taste, then decide if you need more :) Great to add veggies - Peas, Mushrooms, etc...';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1072', `RecipeID`='1072', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Garlic: Saute the minced garlic with the butter in a large nonstick skillet over low heat. Cook for several minutes or until the garlic is soft and fragrant but not browned (browned or burnt garlic will taste bitter). Remove from heat and set aside. Cauliflower: Bring the water or vegetable broth to a boil in a large pot. Add the cauliflower and cook, covered, for 7-10 minutes or until cauliflower is fork tender. Do not drain. Puree: Use a slotted spoon to transfer the cauliflower pieces to the blender. Add 1 cup vegetable broth or cooking liquid, sauteed garlic/butter, salt, pepper, and milk. Blend or puree for several minutes until the sauce is very smooth, adding more broth or milk depending on how thick you want the sauce. You may have to do this in batches depending on the size of your blender. Serve hot! If the sauce starts to look dry, add a few drops of water, milk, or olive oil. more at pinchofyum.com and at www.pinchofyum.com/creamy-cauliflower-sauce';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1073', `RecipeID`='1073', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Remove all of the leaves from the cauliflower and remove the stem, leaving a nice hollow area with the outer part of the head intact. Use toothpicks to hold it together if it starts to fall apart. Drizzle the Salsa down the cracks of the Cauliflower for Blood Fill with Guacamole and Hot Sauce :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1074', `RecipeID`='1074', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a saucepan, mix 1/3 cup of process cheese spread, 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon of prepared mustard, heat at side of grill.';
