REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1084', `RecipeID`='1084', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Heat hot dogs in the microwave for 30 seconds. Chop into bite-sized pieces. 2 In a 9x9 glass baking dish, spread the package of cream cheese. 3 Pour the can of chili over the cream cheese. 4 Place hot dog pieces on top of chili. 5 Place chopped onions on top of hot dog pieces. 6 Sprinkle cheese over top of everything. 7 Heat in microwave on high for 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted and dip is heated through. 8 Serve with Fritos, tortilla chips, or any other of your favorite dippers!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1085', `RecipeID`='1085', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Place nuts in blender container or food processor bowl. Cover; blend or process until finely ground. Add half of the butter and half of the chocolate. 2 Cover and blend again. Add remaining chocolate and butter and the coffee mixture and blend about 3 minutes or until smooth. 3 To store, cover and chill up to 1 month. To serve, let stand at room temperature 1 hour. Makes about 1 cup. 1 tablespoon per serving. 4 For gift giving, layer this rich-tasting spread and additional whole cashews in a crock or pretty jar.';
