REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1182', `RecipeID`='1182', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Crack egg into the bowl of a food processor. 2 Add salt and sugar, and process until well combined. 3 With the motor running, add the oil in a slow, steady stream until all is incorporated. 4 With the machine running, add the rice vinegar. 5 Cover, and refrigerate for at least an hour, before ready to use.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1183', `RecipeID`='1183', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Combine egg yolks and hot water in a bowl and thicken over simmering water, whipping constantly. (Adding a little bit of the lime juice at this point will make the mixture more stable and less liable to break.) When eggs are a smooth custard, remove from heat. Slowly add warm clarified butter, whipping constantly. Add Key lime juice, salt and cayenne pepper. Adjust flavor and consistency.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1184', `RecipeID`='1184', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Mix together the refried beans and chiles. 2 Spread bean mixture into a 8x8 oven proof pan. 3 Layer on black beans and corn. 4 Top with shredded cheese. 5 Bake at 350 for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and dip is bubbly. 6 Serve with tortilla chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1185', `RecipeID`='1185', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='To the bottom of a almost-empty jam or jelly jar, add the other ingredients and shake to combine. Chill in the refrigerator';
