REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1197', `RecipeID`='1197', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 350F Brown hamburger and garlic in a medium skillet over medium/high heat. Crumble as you brown. About half way through, add in the onion and stir to combine. When beef is fully cooked and onion is translucent and fragrant, drain of any excess oil and set aside. In a high powered blender, combine cream cheese, sour cream, mayo, and both cheeses. Pulse until combined. Pour cream cheese mixture into a large bowl and stir in the beef, bacon, pickles, cilantro, and tomatoes. Pour mixture into a prepared baking dish. Sprinkle with more cheese if desired. Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and melty. Serve hot garnished with ketchup and mustard. from USrecipe - more here!';
