REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1210', `RecipeID`='1210', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Chop the green onions. Shred the cheddar cheese. Mix the onions, cheese, mayo, bacon bits, and slivered almonds together. Chill for a couple hours. Serve with Ritz crackers or corn chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1211', `RecipeID`='1211', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Combine the cider vinegar, apple cider, brown sugar, mustard seed, Dijon mustard, tomato paste, salt, black pepper, and neck bones in a heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat Simmer until the sauce thickens, 30 to 40 minutes. Skim any foam from the surface of the liquid and discard. Remove and discard the neck bones. Cool the sauce to room temperature or use immediately.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1212', `RecipeID`='1212', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a medium sauce pan over medium-low heat, whisk together milk and Nutella until the Nutella is melted and milk gets nice and warm. Serve in mugs with the Marshmallows :) Microwave Method: Pour water/milk into microwavable cup and heat for 1-2 min depending on the power of your microwave. Add Nutella and microwave for another minute. Stir and serve.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1213', `RecipeID`='1213', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Drain olives. Beat cream cheese until smooth and creamy. Combine olives, cream cheese, and pecans. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers or chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1214', `RecipeID`='1214', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Drain the oysters and chop into very small pieces. Stir in sour cream. Add salt to taste. Add 1 or 2 teaspoons of Worcestershire sauce and a couple drops of Tabasco sauce, depending on how hot you like it. Mix well and place in refrigerator. Needs to be made several hours ahead for flavor. Serve with potato chips';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1215', `RecipeID`='1215', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Melt Margarine in the microwave Add salt and powder Mix and Enjoy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1216', `RecipeID`='1216', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Melt butter in a medium sauce pan over medium heat. Whisk in the flour to form a roux, cook for 1 to 2 minutes. Slowly pour in the milk and chicken broth while whisking constantly, make sure there are no clumps. Whisk constantly until the mixture begins to thicken, about 5 to 7 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in mustard, Worcestershire sauce, and Parmesan cheese, until the cheese is melted. Season sauce with salt and pepper. Keep the sauce warm.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1217', `RecipeID`='1217', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Stir parmesan cheese into pesto sauce along with olive oil and pour into bowl or serve right out of the jar! Makes an awesome & easy alternative to everyday chip dips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1218', `RecipeID`='1218', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Put all ingredients in a bowl and mix very well with a spoon to get rid of lumps. Cut up fruit to dip in this healthy peanut butter dip alternative!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1219', `RecipeID`='1219', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). 2.In a medium baking dish, mix the pepperoni, cream of mushroom soup and cream cheese. 3.Bake uncovered 15 minutes, or until bubbly and lightly browned';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1220', `RecipeID`='1220', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Finely chop pepperoni and mix with sour cream and seasoned salt. Cover a refrigerate for 2 days to allow pepperoni to soften and the flavors to blend. Serve in hollowed out loaf of bread, surrounded by chunks of bread for dipping. Or with chips.';
