REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1226', `RecipeID`='1226', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a medium bowl, mix together cream cheese, crushed pineapple, onion powder and garlic. Mix in reserved juice from pineapple as desired. Chill in the refrigerator until serving.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1227', `RecipeID`='1227', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Beat the softened cream cheese, with the sour cream, and onion soup mix till well mixed. 2 Stir in the grated cheese and pineapple again mix well. 3 Place in refridgerator until firm enough to hold own shape. 4 Place on a serving plate and mould into hedgehog shape with definite hedgehog nose. 5 Just before serving push corn chips into the dip like the hedgehog bristles. 6 Use grapes, sultanas, raisins or olives for eyes. 7 May need to place extra corn chips and around the hedgehog dip.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1228', `RecipeID`='1228', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 In saucepan, heat pineapple and hot pepper, sugar, and cinnamon; simmer 5 minutes. 2 Take off heat--chill. 3 Serve with tortilla chips (optional, can do over ice cream. Over ice cream is great if you make it hot, hot, hot.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1229', `RecipeID`='1229', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Place the pan and its drippings over medium-low heat. Stir in the sherry, scraping and deglazing the pan. Add the mushroom pieces, continuing to stir. As the sauce thickens, add the water, a little at a time, continuing to stir for 3 or 4 minutes. Stir in the cornstarch-water mixture, increase the heat to medium and stir until the gravy thickens. Taste and adjust seasoning with salt and pepper, if necessary. Yields 3 cups.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1230', `RecipeID`='1230', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 400 degrees. In an oven-safe baking dish, combine all the ingredients reserving approximately 1 TBSP chives, 1/4 C chopped bacon, and 3/4 C shredded cheddar. Stir mixture until well combined. Top with remaining cheese and bacon. Bake for 15-20 minutes, until bubbling and melted. Remove from oven, top with remaining chives. Serve warm with french fries, potato wedges, or ruffled potato chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1231', `RecipeID`='1231', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix together 2 cups mozzarella, cream cheese, ricotta, ⅓ cup Parmesan, Italian seasoning, and red pepper flakes. Season with salt. Transfer mixture to a 9-x-13 baking dish then spread pizza sauce on top. Top with remaining 1 cup mozzarella and pepperoni. Halve biscuits and roll into balls, then place on top of dip. In a small bowl, whisk together oil, garlic, and parsley. Brush on biscuits and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons Parmesan. Bake until biscuits are golden and cheese is melty, about 40 minutes, then cover with aluminum foil and bake until biscuits are cooked through, another 12-15 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes before serving.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1232', `RecipeID`='1232', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Combine all the ingredients, stir well For the meatballs - just pour it all into a crock pot on HIGH for 3 hours until warm :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1233', `RecipeID`='1233', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix the last four ingredients together in a large, non-stick pot. I use my dutch oven. 2DO NOT DRAIN any of the veggies. Dump the liquid in along with everything else. 3Cube the velveeta and add to the canned ingredients. 4Cook over low heat until the velveeta melts. 5Stir often. 6This makes a lot! But, it warms up great in the microwave. 7Serve with chips or use to top enchiladas or even use in quesadillas. 8Variation: Try adding some spicy ground meat or canned chili (with or without beans). Add other veggies like black olives or onion, too.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1234', `RecipeID`='1234', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.In a food processor, combine all ingredients; cover and process until smooth. Transfer to a small bowl; serve immediately.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1235', `RecipeID`='1235', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix all ingredients together in a small bowl.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1236', `RecipeID`='1236', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Toss all ingredients into a large microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on high for 5 minutes, stopping to stir after every minute. The mixture might seem watery during the first few stirs, but should come together as a nice runny dip after all the cheese is melted. Serve immediately as a dip with tortilla chips or as a sauce over your favorite Mexican dish. *Recipe Note: White American cheese is found at most deli counters in your local grocery store. *Reheat Instructions: Store any leftover cheese dip in the fridge. Reheat in the microwave, stirring every 30 seconds until creamy and hot.';
