REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='1266', `RecipeID`='1266', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Slice tomatoes in half. Slice top 1/2 inch off of garlic to expose cloves. Arrange garlic and tomatoes (cut side up) on foil-lined baking dish. Drizzle olive oil over garlic. (This will keep garlic from drying out and getting bitter.) Sprinkle with salt and pepper. 2 Roast in 350 degree oven for 50-60 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool for easier handling. 3 Pour juice out of tomatoes. Discard juice. Squeeze tomato pulp and roasted garlic into blender or food processor. Dicard tomato skins and garlic paper. Blend or process for 5-10 seconds to obtain a smooth consistency.';
