REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='2465', `RecipeID`='2465', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Brown ground beef, Italian sausage, onion and garlic. Add salt, pepper, parsley, oregano, basil, chopped tomatoes with juice, and tomato paste; stirring until well mixed. Cover and simmer 1 hour (or longer,but watch for getting too dry). Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside. Spray a 13 x 9 baking pan with cooking spray. Combine cottage cheese, eggs, pepper, 2 tablespoons parsley, Parmesan cheese and 1/2 1lb of mozzarella cheese; In a lasagna pan, layer noodles, meat sauce, and cheese mixture; repeat. Top off with layer of noodles; sprinkle evenly with remaining mozzarella cheese; make sure to cover noodles completely. Bake at 375 F for 40-60 minutes, or until cheese mixture is thoroughly melted. (I cover w/ foil for about 40 minutes, then uncover for 15-20 minutes) Let sit for 15-20 minutes before cutting and serving. from GoooodRecipes - more here!';
