REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='2925', `RecipeID`='2925', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Heat Oven to 375 Mix Milk and Eggs in a bowl, set aside Layer half of the Potato slices into a buttered casserole dish, salt and pepper Top with the Cheese, Bacon, and the OTHER half of the Potatoes. Pour Egg Mixture over the top Cover with foil and bake for 90 minutes. Let cool for 15 minutes before serving';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='2926', `RecipeID`='2926', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat the oven to 350 F. Mix the melted butter, olive oil, onion, garlic, dijon mustard, and parsley in a bowl. Cut the bread into cubes with X slices without cutting all the way through the bottom crust. Pour the butter-onion garlic mixture carefully into those X cracks using a small spoon and over the top of the bread. Fill those delicious cracks with the grated cheese. (It seems like a lot of work and trouble but its all worth it. Yes.) Wrap the entire loaf with foil, sealing the sides properly and bake for 15-20 minutes. Remove from the oven and unwrap. Bake for another 10 minutes until the cheese is melted and gooey. submitted by JoansFoodWanderings - much more here!';
