REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3272', `RecipeID`='3272', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Beat Egg & milk, you could add pepper or cinnamon if you like. Make a ham & cheese sandwich spreading each slice of bread with mayo to your taste, covering each with at least one slice of cheese, choose one which will melt nicely. Place ham as the middle layer & put the sandwich together. Begin melting a small amount of butter on a skillet or grittle, & dredge the sandwich in the egg mixture, keeping the sandwich together, but soaking up the mixture as if youre making french toast. Fry the sandwich like a grilled cheese on low enough heat to melt & warm the insides, but long enough to brown the bread. This is surprisingly tasty & filling. Enjoy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3273', `RecipeID`='3273', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Prepare and heat grill. Sprinkle one side of each frozen patty with grill seasoning. Place on grill, cover, and cook patties, seasoned sides up, 6 from medium coals for 12-15 minutes, turning once, until thoroughly cooked. Grill split hamburger buns for about 1-2 minutes until browned. Divide cheese sauce among patties. Cover and grill until cheese begins to melt, about 1 minute. Serve on toasted buns with sliced avocado. 4 servings';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3274', `RecipeID`='3274', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Slice bagel in half and toast it, meanwhile you can slice up your tomato and avocado. 2 Spread each side of bagel with 1 Tbsp of cream cheese (or more if you like). 3 Top cream cheese with 1-2 tomato slices, then cover with avocado slices. 4 Finally sprinkle with with lemon pepper to your taste. I would estimate about 1/4 tsp per bagel--but I like a lot! Enjoy! Side note: you can use lime pepper seasoning instead of lemon, and you can get creative with your bagel flavors.';
