REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3312', `RecipeID`='3312', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Shred the crab. Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onion. Cut top 1/3 off bun. Hollow out bun to form shell. Fill with 1/3 cup mixture. Replace top.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3313', `RecipeID`='3313', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Basic Sandwich instructions :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3314', `RecipeID`='3314', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 place ingredients in a bowl, smash together with a fork. 2 Use more mayonnaise as needed for egg size. 3 Serve on bread for a sandwich, English muffins for breakfast, or crackers for an appetizer!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3315', `RecipeID`='3315', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). 2.In a small bowl, combine tuna, minced onion, and black pepper. Divide mixture onto 4 halves of English Muffins. Arrange 3 slices jalapenos on each muffin half. Top each with a slice of Cheddar cheese. Place on baking sheet. 3.Bake in oven for 10 minutes, or until cheese begins to bubble.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3316', `RecipeID`='3316', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 In a large skillet, brown ground beef, celery and onion. 2 Drain the fat, who needs it?. 3 Stir in remaining ingredients, simmer covered, 15-20 minutes, stirring occasionally. 4 If Joes appear too loose, leave cover off and let moisture evaporate. 5 Cook until its the consistency you like for serving on toasted buns, with french fries and cole slaw.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3317', `RecipeID`='3317', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1Brown the beef in a skillet and pour off grease. 2Add the soup (undiluted) and stir. 3Heat until warm. 4Serve on hamburger buns';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3318', `RecipeID`='3318', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix rice together with chili powder, cumin and garlic salt. Add remaining ingredients except for cheese and sour cream. Sprinkle cheese over tortillas, leaving 1/2-inch border around edges, then arrange chicken and rice mixture down the center of each tortilla. (Optional: I like to dollop little bits of sour cream over the cheese before arranging chicken and rice mixture down the center – it makes the wraps delightfully creamy.) Roll stuffed tortillas, leaving edges open and slightly flatten the wraps with the palm of your hand. Spray seam-side of the wrap lightly with cooking spray. Heat a large non-stick skillet (or griddle) over medium heat for 1 minute. Arrange wraps, seam-side down, in pan or griddle and cook until golden brown and crisp, about 2-3 minutes per side. Cooking them seam-side down first helps seal the long edge so they don’t fall apart. Transfer to a plate and repeat with remaining wraps. Serve warm.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3319', `RecipeID`='3319', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.Combine cumin, garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt, chili powder and olive oil together in a bowl. Place shrimp in the bowl and toss to coat. 2.Combine avocado, mayonnaise, chipotle pepper, lime juice and 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt in a food processor. Pulse until smooth. 3.Place shrimp in a skillet over medium heat. Cook until pink and cooked through, about 5 minutes. 4.Toast rolls, if desired. Spread chipotle avocado mayonnaise on the roll. Place lettuce leaves on the bottom half of the roll and place 10 shrimp on each sandwich. more at lifeambrosia.com';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3320', `RecipeID`='3320', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='GoooodRecipes - more here! You can also place them on a baking sheet and bake at 350 for 17 minutes (until golden)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3321', `RecipeID`='3321', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Heat oven to 350°F. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. Separate dough into 8 biscuits. Cut slit on 1 side of 1 biscuit, forming a deep pocket. Place 1 slice of cheese inside pocket. Top cheese with 1 slice of ham and 1 teaspoon honey. Press dough over filling, sealing edge of biscuit; place on cookie sheet. Repeat with remaining biscuits, cheese, ham and honey. Bake 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from cookie sheet to serving plate. Drizzle remaining honey over tops. Serve immediately. Submitted by Pillsbury.com - much more here!!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3322', `RecipeID`='3322', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.Split English muffins in half and toast; set aside. In a small saucepan, heat soup and milk over low heat. 2.Place Canadian bacon in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium high heat until evenly brown. Set aside and keep warm. Add eggs to skillet and cook as desired. 3.Place English muffin halves on serving plates. Top with Canadian bacon and then eggs. Spoon warm soup over eggs.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3323', `RecipeID`='3323', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a 10-inch skillet over medium to high heat, cookbeef and onion until the beef is browned and the onion is tender. Stirring to separate meat. Spoon off fat. Stir in soup, ketchup and black pepper. Reduce heat to low. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serve on buns. Makes 6 servings.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3324', `RecipeID`='3324', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1Mix all the ingredients together. 2Shape mixture into 8 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick. 3Broil or grill the patties 4-inches from the heat, turning once, to the desired doneness, about 10 to 15 minutes.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3325', `RecipeID`='3325', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Butter bread on one side of each piece 2. Place a slice of swiss on one slice of bread. 3. Add sliced apples and slices of bacon. Top off with second slice of cheese and other piece of bread. 4. Add butter to saute pan on medium heat. Add sandwich with butter side of bread into the pan. 5. Cook for 3-4 minutes or until cheese is melted. Flip sandwich and repeat.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3326', `RecipeID`='3326', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='mix ground beef, taco seasoning, water, and hotsauce. make 8 thin patties. place a fair amount of cheese right in the middle of 4 of the patties, placing the other four on top, sealing the edges of each patty, to where they form one large one. heat the butter, or oil in a large skillet. use a bacon press, if you have one to help flatten the patty once its in the pan. If not, use castiron skillet... they work great, maybe a heavy plate? lol. the point is to not make the meat of the burger fairly thin, otherwise... all the toppings will fall off, and youll lose more than you get to eat. toast buns in the oven, by broiling... inside up, for about 3 minutes. remove buns; place patty on top, add some sour cream, a little more shredded cheese, then go crazy with toppings!!!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3327', `RecipeID`='3327', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a large skillet, brown ground beef over medium high heat. Add in taco seasoning and stir to combine. Remove from heat. Spread butter on one side of each slice of bread. On the non-buttered side, add lettuce, tomatoes, ground beef and cheese and cover with other slice of buttered bread. The buttered side should be facing outwards. Heat a skillet to medium-high heat. Grill each side for 2 to 3 minutes or until desired doneness is reached. Cut in half and enjoy hot. Serve with salsa, guacamole and sour cream for dipping.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3328', `RecipeID`='3328', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Cook your ground beef in a skillet over medium high heat and add taco seasoning. set aside Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray. Slice rolls like you would a burger bun and place bottom half in the pan and set the top half aside. Spread sour cream over the bottoms of the rolls, evenly spread prepared taco meat out on the sour cream. Sprinkle the taco meat with 1 cup of the shredded cheese. Evenly distribute peppers and tomatoes on the cheese and cover with the remaining cup of cheese. Place roll tops back on the top, stir together melted butter, onion powder, garlic powder, and crushed red pepper and pour evenly over the tops of the rolls. Cover with aluminum let set for 10 minutes, then bake for 10 minutes.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3329', `RecipeID`='3329', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='slather some mayo on that bread slice up that tomato and pile it up on that bread slather some mayo on another piece of bread put that piece of bread on top of that other piece of bread (which is already piled high with tomato slices) eat that sandwich up while you pump your fist';
