REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3333', `RecipeID`='3333', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Toast bread (if desired). 2 Put Mayo on slices of bread. 3 Layer with Cucumber slices. 4 Sprinkle Salt and Pepper, if desired. 5 Layer with tomato slices. 6 Put on the top piece of bread, and cut. 7 Enjoy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3334', `RecipeID`='3334', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.On each bagel or muffin half, sprinkle half of the cheddar cheese and cayenne pepper. Top with a tomato slice. Sprinkle half of the Parmesan cheese over each tomato. Broil 6 in. from the heat for 4-5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3335', `RecipeID`='3335', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 400°. Slice roma tomatoes in half and toss with olive oil and salt. Place on a covered baking tray and roast for 40-50 minutes. Tomatoes should be soft and beginning to brown. In a food processor, add clove of garlic and pulse until minced. Add in roasted tomatoes and basil. Pulse until mixture is spreadable. In a skillet, cook eggs. For a sandwich I usually prefer a fried egg with the yolk broken but scrambled would work just as well (or for an even messier sandwich, over-easy.) Lightly brush olive oil on outside parts of bread and assemble sandwich with cheese, spread, and egg (I usually do cheese on the outside edge and spread/eggs on the inside. Cook over medium-low in a skillet until cheese is melted and outsides are toasted, 10-15 minutes. much more at http://naturallyella.com/roasted-tomato-and-egg-grilled-cheese-sandwich/';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3336', `RecipeID`='3336', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Combine the beef, tortilla chips, ranch dressing, salt and pepper; mix well. 2 Divide into 4 equal patties. 3 In large skillet, fry burgers over med-high for 10 minutes each side, or until no longer pink. 4 Toast the bread. 5 Serve burgers on toast dressed with your favorite condiments.';
