REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3352', `RecipeID`='3352', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1-In a pan on medium heat, melt butter. 2-Add onion, mixing into butter. 3-Once the onions begin the soften, add garlic, thyme and rosemary. 4-Saute for a couple of minutes. 5-Sprinkle about a tbsp of flour, mixing in. 6- Once mixed in, add wine. 7- Reduce until alcohol has burned off and the reduction is thick enough to coat a spoon. Taste reduction to ensure alcohol has burned off. 8- Spread reduction on each slice of bread. 9- Add Gruyere. 10- Butter the outside of each slice. 11- Grill in a pan on medium heat until golden brown on each side. Serve!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3353', `RecipeID`='3353', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 350. Spray a 9x13 baking dish with cooking spray.Combine chili and salsa. Place hot dog in tortilla and add a spoon full of chili mixture to each. Roll and place seam side down in baking dish. Add tomato/enchilada sauce to remaining chili mixture and pour over tortillas and spread evenly. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350 for 25-30 mins. Let stand for 5-10 mins before serving. Top with jalapenos or salsa if desired.';
