REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3387', `RecipeID`='3387', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Boil the pasta with a handful of salt - Cook Halfway then drain Working in batches, transfer some bowties into a skillet with about 1/2 cup hot vegetable oil. When they are golden - remove from the pan and toss with salt, lemon, and Parmesan. Repeat until theyre all done :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3388', `RecipeID`='3388', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Set oven to 400 degrees - then watch carefully, cooking time varies depending on how crispy you want your bacon, (10-15 minutes) fill with WHATEVER YOU WANT!!!! Tip - If you want BIGGER cups (and you dont have a king muffin pan) just throw a LOOSELY balled up piece of aluminum foil on top of the flipped muffin pan. Another advantage: it makes removing them from the muffin pan easier since you can just pull the ball off the top. Make sure its loosely balled up so when you go to remove the aluminum foil, you can just squeeze it down til it comes out easily STEP BY STEP - CLICK HERE!!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3389', `RecipeID`='3389', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Spread the heated beans on a warm tortilla. 2 Place a frankfurter on top. 3 Sprinkle with cheese and roll up the tortilla. 4 Microwave for 2 minutes or place in preheated 350°F oven for about 10 minutes. 5 Serve with the salsa of your choice.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3390', `RecipeID`='3390', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In the Ziploc bag add all of the ingredients except for the crackers. Close up the ZipLoc Bag and mix ingredients well by shaking the bag. Add all 4 sleeves of Saltine Crackers and close the bag. Turn the bag over several times to coat crackers with the chile and oil mixture. Let the bag rest for a couple of hours, turning the bag every 15 minutes or so. If you can wait til the next day, they are even better. This is one you can make ahead of your party and it will keep really well';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3391', `RecipeID`='3391', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='-Cut apple in half -Scoop out the middle - squeeze a little lemon juice on them to prevent browning -Make the Caramel Sauce - (your favorite recipe - I just like to melt the candy ones) -Before you pour the caramel into the apple, make sure you wipe out the apple with a paper towel - if the apple is too wet the caramel wont stick. -Pour the Caramel (any extra toppings you feel) -Chill in the fridge until the caramel sets (bout 30 minutes) - Slice and enjoy :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3392', `RecipeID`='3392', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Prepare chicken (easier if its already cooked, i.e. tyson) Dip in caramel sauce.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3393', `RecipeID`='3393', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Peel carrots into thick slices 2. Toss slices in olive oil and salt 3. Bake at 350 for 12 minutes 4. Cool and Enjoy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3394', `RecipeID`='3394', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a medium bowl, combine riced cauliflower, basil, eggs and mozzarella. Divide into 4 amounts and press evenly on the parchment paper. *you can omit the basil or sub it for others herbs of your choice. Bake the crusts at 450 degrees for 12-15 minutes.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3395', `RecipeID`='3395', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Break a head of cauliflower into popcorn-like, bite-size florets Spread them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Spray the cauliflower lightly with olive oil, then sprinkle with red pepper flakes, freshly ground pepper, and sea salt. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 425 degrees F or until the cauliflower is slightly browned.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3396', `RecipeID`='3396', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix all together and store in airtight container.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3397', `RecipeID`='3397', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Melt butter in large pot, add cereal and stir well. Add cheese and mix well over low heat. Pour on foil and seperate to cool. Yields 6 cups.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3398', `RecipeID`='3398', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Place cheese, mustard and beer in bowl and press cheese down until it is covered by beer. Cover and let stand for one hour at room temperature. Cream butter in food processor or mixer. Add cheese, beer mixture and all other ingredients. Season to taste with additional pepper or salt, if desired. Pack into crocks or other bowls and refrigerate for up to two weeks. Serve at room temperature with crackers.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3399', `RecipeID`='3399', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Unroll croissant dough and cut into squares (if you bought the kind that is pre-cut into triangles then form squares by glueing two of them together with a little water). Spread cream cheese as thickly as you want onto the dough and sprinkle chives on top. Roll dough up like a jelly roll (rolling it in a crescent shape will make the cheese run out while baking). Pinch the edges closed if you want. Bake according to directions on dough package.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3400', `RecipeID`='3400', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 350º. Place a sheet of parchment paper on a metal cookie sheet. DO NOT use a silicone/silpat sheet, waxed paper or foil (unless it’s the special non-stick foil) to bake these or they will not cook properly. Using a tablespoon, scoop up 1 T. of cheese and make a small pile on the parchment. Press it slightly flat. Repeat 15 more times. Place a slice of jalapeno on top of each pile. Pop into 350º oven for about 10-12 minutes. Recommend browning them a bit more than shown in the photo for a firmer snack to serve at parties. These are somewhat pliable if under browned. Allow them to completely cool and fully firm up before removing from the pan for best results. from MitEasyRecipes - more here!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3401', `RecipeID`='3401', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Set oven to broil 2. Grease a baking sheet 3. Slice half an Avocado (I did it in strips) and place onto slices of bread. 4. Top avocado with Garlic and Onion Seasoning and Salt and spoon out Diced Tomatos leaving a little room around the edges so that they do not spill over while in oven. 5. Top the Diced tomatoes strategically with the Cheddar Cheese and again leave room for melting. 6. Place in heated oven for about 5 minutes (check regularly). When cheese is browned it is ready.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3402', `RecipeID`='3402', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. 2 In cup, mix cumin, chili powder, and salt. 3 Spray 1 side of each tortilla with cooking spray, sprinkle with chili powder mixture. 4 Cut each tortilla into 8 wedges and place on ungreased large non-stick cookie sheet. 5 Bake tortillas 8 to 10 minutes until crisp, cool on wire rack. 6 If not serving right away, store in tightly covered container. 7 Serve withFresh and Chunky Salsa (youll find the recipe underLow sodium, low cholesterol dips on this web site).';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3403', `RecipeID`='3403', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Just mix it all together an enjoy';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3404', `RecipeID`='3404', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Preheat the oven to 400°F. 2 Lay the tortilla chips on a cookie sheet. 3 Toss together the cheese, chilies, and onion, and sprinkle over the tortilla chips. 4 Bake for about 5 minutes, until the cheese has melted. 5 Serve hot';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3405', `RecipeID`='3405', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Whisk the egg white in a cup. Pour the egg whites over the nuts, stirring until the nuts are coated with egg white. 2. In a small bowl, stir the cinnamon, vanilla, sugar, and salt together. Add the cinnamon sugar mixture to the nuts, a little a time, while stirring. 3. Spread the coated nuts on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes without stirring. Use a spatula to remove the nuts from the hot baking sheet immediately. Allow to cool thoroughly before storing in tightly closed container. Store in a cool place. more at Justgetoffyourbuttandbake.com';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3406', `RecipeID`='3406', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Set oven to High 2. Spread butter onto one side of bread. I use a lot because I like to soften the bread more. 3. Sprinkle about 2 Tablespoons of sugar directly on the buttered side of bread. 4. Sprinkle about 1 Tablespoon of cinnamon directly on the buttered side of bread. 5. Pop it in the oven and watch for the cinnamon and sugar to mix with the melting butter. 6. ENJOY! **it is okay to do many of these at the same time.**';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3407', `RecipeID`='3407', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Preheat an oven to 350*. 2 Brush the butter evenly over the pita. 3 Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon evenly over the pita. 4 Cut into strips or wedges (a pizza slicer works really well). 5 Place on baking sheet and bake for 5-8 minutes, or until crsipy and slightly golden (watch, ovens can vary). 6 Cool and serve with vanilla ice cream.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3408', `RecipeID`='3408', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Place Ritz cracker salt side down and top with a little ketchup. 2 Add cheese and pepperoni. 3 Heat in microwave until cheese melts. (usually less than 30 seconds)!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3409', `RecipeID`='3409', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Take soft tortillas and spread with a two spoonfuls of sauce. 2 Add some cheese and toppings. 3 Roll up into cigar shapes rolls and bake at 200 degrees until warm all the way through.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3410', `RecipeID`='3410', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.In a large heatproof bowl, combine corn chips and peanuts. In a small saucepan, combine the brown sugar, corn syrup and butter. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Pour over corn chip mixture; toss to coat. Transfer to a greased 15-in. x 10-in. x 1-in. baking pan. Bake at 250 degrees F for 30-40 minutes; stirring every 15 minutes. Spread onto waxed paper; cool. Break apart and store in airtight containers.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3411', `RecipeID`='3411', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Spread or pat cream cheese around each pickle. Wrap 2 sheets of meat around each pickle. Refrigerate pickles overnight, slice before serving.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3412', `RecipeID`='3412', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1) In a microwaveable bowl, put the cream cheese and a splash of milk/ half and half. Microwave until cream cheese is melted. Look around then eat some melted cream cheese. I know you want to. I know it. 2) Drain canned chicken. dont worry if theres some liquid left. Its fine. Calm down. Add the chicken to the bowl with the cream cheese. Stir that thing. 3) Add as much taco seasoning (and however much Red Taco sauce as you want if youre using that) as you want to. dont put too much. Unless you want to. You know what, do what you want. This recipe doesnt even have exact measurements. Do what you want. 4) If it tastes good, slap it into a tortilla. Feel free to microwave it if its not warm enough at this point. Or set it on fire. Whatever you want. 5) Shove it in your face. Make omnomnom noises because its fun. Then they lived happily ever after. The End. :D *rainbows*';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3413', `RecipeID`='3413', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Prepare the sizes of your Tortillas, use a small plate as a template to cut the smaller ones Brown/Chop up your ground beef in a skillet Stir in Taco Seasoning Heat up Re-Fried Beans Lay the Larger Tortilla Flat Spread Beans and/or Cheese in the Center Lay corn Tortilla on top of the Beans Add any other toppings you like. Guacamole, Sour Cream, Salsa work great to hold everything together inside Lay Smaller Tortilla on top Fold the edges of the Larger Tortilla up and around the smaller one. Spray the outside with Cooking spray Cook, seam side down, in a skillet until brown Flip, and cook until brown Serve!!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3414', `RecipeID`='3414', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Put graham crackers in zip-lock bag and then put coolwhip in same bag. I prefer no peaches, but the original recipe calls for peaches. If peaches are wanted, add them into the bag as well. Tightly close the bag and make sure to get all of the air out. Crush up contents in hand until they are soft and creamy. Lastly, when ready to eat (recommended that it is cold) cut a tiny hole at 1 of the bottom corners of the bag. Then squeeze into mouth! VERY DELICIOUS,EASY, AND FUN!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3415', `RecipeID`='3415', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='8 hot dogs 8 slices bread 8 slices American cheese ketchup and mustard to taste';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3416', `RecipeID`='3416', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Place one cheese pizza on a greased baking sheet. Cut sausage-links into 1/4-inch-think slices. Arrange sausage slices and olives on top. Sprinkle with half of the cheese. Top with remaining cheese pizza, crust side up. Cover the entire pizza with foil. Bake in a 375 degree F oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 10 minutes more. Sprinkle the remaining mozzarella cheese over pizza. Bake 5 minutes more or until cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3417', `RecipeID`='3417', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Halve or quarter the strawberries, depending on their size; place on a baking sheet; season with salt and pepper; Dry in the oven for three hours at 100° C / 210° F. from theworldwidegourmet.com';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3418', `RecipeID`='3418', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Stir together garlic, ginger, and soy sauce; set aside for five minutes to allow the flavors to blend. Cut the avocado in half, and discard the pit; divide the sauce between the avocado halves. Eat with a spoon!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3419', `RecipeID`='3419', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Preheat oven to 400 degrees In large bowl, combine pancake mix, apple sauce, ricotta, butter, and water. Mix well with fork or pastry cutter. Once desired consistency has been reached, transfer dough to lightly floured surface. Roll dough out to 1/2 thickness and use glass or biscuit cutter to cut biscuits. Grease baking sheet with cooking spray and back 9-12 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm and enjoy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3420', `RecipeID`='3420', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='HEAT oven to 300ºF. Line large shallow roasting pan with heavy foil, extending foil over edges of pan. Butter foil. REMOVE all unpopped popcorn. Pour popcorn into prepared pan. Keep warm in oven. COMBINE sweetened condensed milk and dry gelatin in medium saucepan. Heat and stir over low heat until mixture is slightly thickened and bubbly, 4 to 5 minutes. POUR mixture over popcorn. Stir gently to coat using a long-handled wooden spoon. Bake 20 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes. Carefully turn out onto large piece of lightly buttered foil. Cool. Break into pieces or clusters.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3421', `RecipeID`='3421', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Preheat oven to 425 degrees. 2 Lightly spray cookie sheet and set aside. 3 Spray each tortilla shell lightly on each side; sprinkle lightly with popcorn salt. 4 Using kitchen scissors (or knife), cut into one inch wide strips (if using for tortilla soup) or cut into wedges (if using to dip with). 5 Put on cookie sheets in one layer, laying as close to each other as possible without overlapping. 6 Bake at 425 degrees for just a few minutes (3 to 4 minutes watching closely for burning) till they turn a very light brown. 7 Remove and enjoy hot or cold.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3422', `RecipeID`='3422', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1) Fill a small, medium or large pan 3/4 full with tapwater (depending on how many eggs you desire to cook). 2) Place on the stove over High heat. 3) Once water reaches a boil, place desired quantity of eggs in the water using a Tablespoon or measuring cup. Turn heat down to med-high to prevent overflow. 4) Let eggs BOIL for 5 minutes then SHUT THE HEAT OFF and let them sit in the hot water for 15 more minutes. 5) After 15 minutes, run cold water into the pan until only cool water is left. Crack and peel your beautifully cooked, perfect eggs. 6) Sprinkle with salt and/or pepper for a snack or use in any recipe calling for hard boiled eggs! ENJOY!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3423', `RecipeID`='3423', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Lay one tortilla on a cookie sheet. 2 Spread cheese over the tortilla, being careful not to spill it out onto the cookie sheet. 3 Cover with second tortilla. 4 Bake at 350 degrees (F) for about 10 minutes, or until tortilla begins to turn golden brown. 5 Cut with a pizza cutter into quarters (or eighths) and serve hot with salsa, sour cream or quacamole.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3424', `RecipeID`='3424', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Combine the flour, baking powder and salt. In a food processor pulse the flour with the cold butter until you get a crumbly mixture. Transfer to a bowl. Add the egg and milk and knead in to form a sort of dough. Dump the dough onto a lightly floured surface and bring together into a ball. Pat into a circle of 1 inch thickness, wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3425', `RecipeID`='3425', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Not that I have to tell you how... but here you go :) Dividing evenly, spread peanut butter on muffin halves. Sprinkle with wheat germ; then top with apple slices. Serve open-faced.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3426', `RecipeID`='3426', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Snap off asparagus ends. 2 Boil asparagus until tender, drain, and set aside. 3 Add olive oil and garlic to saute pan. 4 Saute for 1 minute until garlic is fragrant. 5 Add aspargus back to pan, saute for 3 minutes. 6 Add pepper to taste. 7 Remove fron pan and sprinkle with feta cheese.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3427', `RecipeID`='3427', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix all the ingredients together, except for the tortillas. Spread the mix onto the tortillas. Roll the tortillas up. Place in fridge for 15-30 min. so they can firm up. Slice into 1/4 in rolls. Eat and enjoy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3428', `RecipeID`='3428', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.Heat oven to 425° F. 2.Spread the fries on a baking sheet. Bake until golden, about 25 minutes. 3.Meanwhile, cook the ground beef in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until no trace of pink remains, 8 to 10 minutes. 4.Spoon off any excess fat. Add the marinara sauce and cook until warmed through. 5.Transfer to an 8-by-11-inch or 8-inch square baking dish. Top with the fries. If desired, return to oven for 5 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3429', `RecipeID`='3429', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Mix together bread crumbs, salt, and pepper. Set aside in a shallow dish. 2 Shape macaroni and cheese into 8 balls with a piece of hot dog in the center. Roll in the bread crumb mixture coating well. 3 Fry in a pan with 350 degree oil until golden brown. Drain on a paper towel to remove excess oil.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3430', `RecipeID`='3430', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='HowWeLearn.com - much more here!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3431', `RecipeID`='3431', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Picture says it all :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3432', `RecipeID`='3432', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Line a muffin pan with paper liners, or use a silicone muffin pan for easy removal. Mash the bananas. Add wet ingredients and cocoa powder and mix well. Add all other ingredients, mix well then press into prepared muffin tin. Freeze at least 60 minutes before serving.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3433', `RecipeID`='3433', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Heat a small skillet over med-high. Once hot, add all ingredients. Stir frequently until syrup is caramelized, about 4-5 minutes. Let cool.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3434', `RecipeID`='3434', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Slice the avocado in half and remove the stone. Prick all over with a fork, or cut criss-cross patterns with a knife. This allows the sauce to penetrate the flesh. 2. Pour the sauce over each half, then top with lime juice and salt and pepper. 3. In the cavity where the stone has been, put a fourth of the cheese on each avocado half. Place under the hot grill for 2 minutes. 4. Top with remaining cheese and grill (broil for Americans!) for another 2 minutes until completely melted and avocado warmed through. Eat hot with a wedge of lime and more hot sauce on the side!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3435', `RecipeID`='3435', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='On a toothpick, sword, etc... skewer Grape, Banana, Strawberry, and top with the Marshmallow. Cute and Easy!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3436', `RecipeID`='3436', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='mix all ingredients in bowl and beat.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3437', `RecipeID`='3437', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Halloween Fun Club!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3438', `RecipeID`='3438', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Microwave butter, blend in seasonings. Add pretzelsto toss and coat. Heat in microwave, 1 1/2 minutes, stirring halfway through.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3439', `RecipeID`='3439', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Mix flour, baking powder and shortening; add milk an blend well. 2 Form a ball of dough and cut into four pieces. 3 Roll dough out very thin. 4 Cut with a cookie cutter or the top of a glass (wet the glass first). 5 Place on cookie sheet. Prick with a fork 4-5 times and sprinkle with salt. 6 Bake at 375 degrees 8 to 10 minutes or until golden (watch crackers carefully so they dont burn).';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3440', `RecipeID`='3440', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Cut (triangles) 2. Butter 3. Bake till crisp';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3441', `RecipeID`='3441', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the paddle attachment, mix the cheddar, butter, and salt until soft and combined. Add the flour and mix on low speed (the dough will be dry and pebbly). Slowly add the water and continue to mix as the dough forms a ball. Pat the dough into a disk, wrap tightly with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for at least an hour. Preheat the oven to 375F. Line two baking sheets with parchment paper. Divide the dough into two pieces and roll each into a very thin (1/8 inch or less) 10 x 12-inch rectangle. Using a fluted pastry cutter or sharp knife, cut the rectangles into 1-inch squares, then transfer to the baking sheets. Use the tip of a chopstick to punch a hole into the center of each square. Bake for 15-17 minutes or until puffed and browning at the edges. Watch carefully, as the high fat content of the crackers makes it a fine line between golden delicious and burnt. Immediately move the crackers to racks to cool. more at achowlife.com';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3442', `RecipeID`='3442', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Fill crock-pot with your favorite cereal, pretzels, and nuts. In a sauce pan - melt butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic and onion powders, sugar, dissolve. Pour mix over the chex mix, cover, and cook for 2 1/2 hours on LOW. Stir every 30 minutes to make sure the mix gets everywhere';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3443', `RecipeID`='3443', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In bowl of food processor, combine flours, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Pulse a few times. Add the cold butter and pulse until texture is dry and crumbly. In a separate bowl, mix together the honey, molasses and water. Add to food processor and blend together until it forms a ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for one hour. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Roll the dough out on a well floured surface (I used all purpose). Roll the dough out pretty thin and cut with cookie cutters or cut into rectangles. Make fork marks in the dough. Transfer to baking sheets lined with parchment paper (Thats what I use, just a baking sheet would work fine). You could sprinkle these with sugar or cinnamon/sugar before baking. Bake for 11-14 minutes until golden and crisp.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3444', `RecipeID`='3444', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='To Make the Glaze: Place powdered sugar in bowl. Pour milk slowly until it has a consistency of really thick syrup. Make the Pie Crust Combine flour and salt in bowl. Add shortening or butter and blend with fork, pastry cutter or your fingers until mixture is fairly coarse. Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, gently mixing dough after each addition until dough forms a ball. (Dough can also be prepared in food processor. Use the pulse button just until it starts to pull away from the sides. Be very careful not to overwork the dough.) Place dough on a lightly floured surface and roll into a square/rectangle. Cut out long strips about 2 inches wide, and 3 inches long. Repeat till you run out of dough. submitted by BakeMore.Wordpress.com - much more here!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3445', `RecipeID`='3445', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='If potatoes are old, peel and slice thin, 1/16 in thickness, slicing across the potato. If the potatoes are new or good skins, DO NOT PEEL, just scrub well, then slice them 1/16 in thickness, slicing across the potato. Sprinkle with your choice of spices or herbs or just leave them plain. If you have a microwave bacon tray, place the sliced potatoes flat on the tray in a single layer. Cover with a microwaveable, round heavy plastic cover. Microwave on HIGH (full power) for 7 to 8 minutes. Cooking time could vary slightly, depending on the wattage of your microwave. You do not have to turn the sliced potatoes over. If you do not have a bacon tray, use a microwave safe casserole dish. Rub the inside of the dish with some olive oil for the first batch of potato chips. I do not know why, but I find that if you do not rub oil the first time, some chips will tend to stick to the dish. After the first batch is done, you do not have to rub the dish again. Continue to microwave the remainder of sliced potatoes as noted above. NOTE: You can also use PARCHMENT PAPER to place your potato slices. Place your potato slices, then sprinkle them with whatever you like and then place another piece of parchment paper on top. This will help microwave the potatoes more evenly and they should turn out nice and crisp. ADDITIONAL SEASONING IDEAS: Granulated garlic powder with parsley. Cracked black pepper, grated parmesan and sea salt sprinkled after removing from microwave.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3446', `RecipeID`='3446', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Slice potatoes into 1/8-inch rounds for thicker potato chips. For thinner ones, use a mandolin to cut very thin slices. Toss slices in a medium bowl with oil and salt to coat evenly. Coat a large microwave-proof plate with cooking spray. Arrange some potato slices in a single layer on the plate. Microwave, uncovered, on High until some slices start to brown, 2 to 3 minutes (depending upon potato thickness and microwave power). Turn slices over (they will be hot, so take care with your fingers) and continue microwaving until they start to crisp and brown around the edges, about 35 seconds for very thin potato slices to 2 to 4 minutes for thicker slices. Check frequently and rearrange slices as needed to prevent scorching. Transfer chips to another plate and allow to cool completely. (They will crisp up more as they cool.) Repeat process with remaining slices. Storage: Store in an airtight container for up to 3 days.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3447', `RecipeID`='3447', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Sprinkle confectioners sugar on 2 (15 x 11-inch) lipped cookie sheets Combine sugar, syrup and water in a heavy saucepan and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Continue to cook without stirring until syrup reaches 290 F on a candy thermometer. (It works best to have a snap-on thermometer and it can take up to 45-50 minutes to reach that temperature) Remove from heat and add food coloring (and/or flavors) - TRY NOT TO INHALE over the boiling liquid! Pour onto cookie sheets, cool and break into small pieces.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3448', `RecipeID`='3448', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a bowl mix together flour, sugar, salt and paprika. Using a regular sized cheese grater, grate butter into flour mixture (or cut in with pastry cutter or knives). Immediately toss butter in flour mixture to coat, breaking up pieces a bit more as you go. Mix together water and vanilla. Pour over flour mixture and mix until evenly moistened and the dough comes together but is not sticky (add a bit more water if necessary). Divide the mixture in half and form into balls. On a lightly floured piece of parchment paper, roll out the dough as thinly as possible (or as desired). Cut into squares and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Sprinkle with a bit of salt (and other toppings if desired). Bake at 400º F for 8-10 minutes or until browned and crisp. Cool completely and store in an air-tight container or bag at room temperature.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3449', `RecipeID`='3449', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. In large mixing bowl, combine the flours and thoroughly mix. 2. In separate bowl blend the oil, salt, and water. 3. Add liquid mixture to dry, mixing well but as little as possible. 4. Roll as thin as possible on unoiled cookie sheet - not more than 1/8” thick. Mark with knife for size crackers desired, but do not cut through. Prick each cracker a few times with fork. Sprinkle lightly with salt or onion salt, if desired. 5. Bake at 350F until crisp and light brown, about 30 minutes. 6. When cool, separate into individual crackers. You can separate before baking if you want - its harder to separate, but you have control over the size of the chips.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3450', `RecipeID`='3450', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Place ground chuck (and hot dogs if desired) in a medium saucepan and cover with water. 2 Boil the water until the meat is cooked. 3 Drain the ground chuck and then return the meat to the saucepan. 4 Add ketchup and chili powder (more if desired) to the meat. 5 Cook over low heat until the chili is warmed through.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3451', `RecipeID`='3451', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='In a large saucepan, melt the butter. Then add the marshmallows and stir until completely melted and smooth. Remove from heat and add the cereal. Stir until coated evenly. Spread the mixture into a 13x9x2 inch pan. While cooling, cut up candy bars into small pieces. Sprinkle over top and voila! Let cool enough to set up and EAT!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3452', `RecipeID`='3452', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='split into small pieces and spread on a baking sheet. add oil and seasning as you like but not too much oil not to soak it! you can mix it a little bit put in the oven at broil 5 min max!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3453', `RecipeID`='3453', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Slice loaf in half lengthwise. Scoop out the loaf Generously butter the inside of the loaf to prevent it from betting soggy. dont miss any spots Combine th ecottage cheese, onions, and some of the scopped bread and mayonnaise if desired Stuff and refill the bread, salt and papper to taste Sprinkle on the crumbled bacon, tomatoes, cucumbers and parsley Put the top of th eloaf on, and refrigerate until ready';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3454', `RecipeID`='3454', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1. Preheat oven to 325 2. Mix ingredients and spread on baking dish 3. Bake for 30 min 4. Cut into Squares (1 1/4 inch)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3455', `RecipeID`='3455', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Let cool on a rack for 6-8 hours in a cool oven. To store, keep loosely in a bag or a plastic container in the refrigerator or on the counter. Best used within a week of preparation. After chips have dried substantially, in a plastic container toss with popcorn seasoning for desired flavor. 12 Chips is a Serving submitted by YourLighterSide.com - more details here!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3456', `RecipeID`='3456', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='grease the pan with the butter. While the pan is heating up, cut up the lunch meat into small pieces. Put the first tortilla on the pan, and put the cheese and the meat on top of it. Cover it with the second tortilla. Cook untill both tortillas are golden brown.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3457', `RecipeID`='3457', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Between two sheets of wax paper, roll out each biscuit into a 6-in. circle with a rolling pin or a large soup can. It might be difficult, because the dough is springy, but press kind of hard. 2 In a small, nonstick skillet over medium-low to medium heat, cook each biscuit for 60 seconds on each side, or until golden brown. 3 DO NOT put any oil in the pan. Cook them in a completely dry pan. 4 Stack the bread on a plate and cover with foil to keep warm';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3458', `RecipeID`='3458', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1-Combine the water, sugar, yeast, and butter in the bowl of a stand mixer and mix with the dough hook until combined. Let sit for 5 minutes. 2-Add the salt and flour and mix on low speed until combined. Increase the speed to medium and continue kneading until the dough is smooth and begins to pull away from the side of the bowl, about 3 to 4 minutes. If the dough appears too wet, add additional flour, 1 tablespoon at a time. 3 -Remove the dough from the bowl, place on a flat surface and knead into a ball with your hands. 4- Oil a bowl with vegetable oil, add the dough and turn to coat with the oil. 5- Cover with a clean towel or plastic wrap and place in a warm spot until the dough doubles in size, about 1 hour. 6- Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F. 7- Bring the water to a boil in a small roasting pan over high heat and add the baking soda. 8- Remove the dough from the bowl and place on a flat surface. 9- Divide the dough into 8 equal pieces, about 4 1/4 to 4 1/2 ounces each. 10-Roll each piece into a long rope and shape into the lengths or shapes that you want (sticks are easy and tasty). 11- Boil the pretzels in the water solution in batches. Boil for about 30 seconds. Remove with a large slotted spoon. 12- Place pretzels on a baking sheet that has been sprayed with cooking spray. Make sure they are not touching. 13- Brush the tops with the egg wash and season liberally with the salt. 14- Place into the oven and bake for 15 to 18 minutes until golden brown. 15- Add additional toppings immediately after they come out of the oven. More at LeeCooks.com';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3459', `RecipeID`='3459', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Jans Sushi Bar - click here for more!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3460', `RecipeID`='3460', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 split bagel in half 2 spread salsa over each half. 3 top each with avacado. 4 then with a slice of tasty cheese. 5 place under the grill for 5 minutes or until cheese melts';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3461', `RecipeID`='3461', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 If potatoes are old, peel and slice thin, less than 1/16 in thickness (paper thin), slicing across the potato. 2 If the potatoes are new or good skins, DO NOT PEEL, just scrub well, then slice them less than 1/16 in thickness (paper thin), slicing across the potato. 3 Place potato slices in a bowl, sprinkle with some salt (if desired) cover with cold water and let sit for 10 minutes. 4 Remove potato slices in batches onto paper toweling and pat dry. 5 If you have a microwave bacon tray, rub the tray with a vegetable oil, then place the sliced potatoes flat on the tray in a single layer. 6 Sprinkle with your choice of herbs or spices or just leave them plain. 7 Cover with a microwaveable, round heavy plastic cover. 8 Microwave on HIGH (full power) for 5 to 5 1/2 minutes or until they curl slightly and are a very light brown in color. 9 Cooking time could vary slightly, depending on the wattage of your microwave and the thickness of the slices. The thinner the slices, the quicker they cook and the tastier they are. 10 You do not have to turn the sliced potatoes over. 11 If you do not have a bacon tray, use a microwave safe casserole dish. 12 Rub the inside of the dish with some olive oil for the first batch of potato chips. 13 I do not know why, but I find that if you do not rub oil the first time, some chips will tend to stick to the dish. 14 After the first batch is done, you do not have to rub the dish again. 15 Continue to microwave the remainder of sliced potatoes as noted above. 16 If using a bacon tray, after the first batch is cooked, you can reduce the microwaving time to 4 1/2 minutes and even less as you continue to microwave each batch. 17 NOTE: You can also use PARCHMENT PAPER to microwave the potato slices. Lightly spray or rub the parchment paper with some vegetable oil or a Pam spray. Place your potato slices on the parchment paper, then sprinkle them with whatever you like and then place another piece of parchment paper on top. This will help microwave the potatoes more evenly and they should turn out nice and crisp. Microwaving time should be between 5 and 6 minutes.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3462', `RecipeID`='3462', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='First, start with Bisquick baking mix, milk and eggs. This makes the base for all mini pies. Combine and start with a little less than at tablespoon in each greased muffin cup. Next - add your Veggie Mixture to each cup. bout 1/4 cup Then top it off with one more tablespoon of the Bisquick Mixture Bake for 25-30 minutes at 375 (until golden brown) and BAM! youre all done :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3463', `RecipeID`='3463', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Arranged Triscuit crackers on a paper towel covered plate (approx. 30) Spread pizza sauce onto the crackers Sprinkle cheese on top Microwave for 30 seconds And BOOM! Tasty mini Triscuit Pizzas!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3464', `RecipeID`='3464', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 In a small bowl, beat the egg with 1-tablespoon of the bread crumbs. 2 Dip the cheese cubes into the egg mixture and then roll in the bread crumbs to coat well. 3 In a large skillet, melt just enough oil to make a 3-inch depth. 4 Heat to 380-degrees. 5 Fry the cheese cubes, a few at a time, for 1 minute or until crisp and golden. 6 Lift out with a slotted spoon and drain on a paper towel. 7 Keep warm until ready to serve. 8 Serve with toothpicks. 9 Makes: about 1 dozen. 10(*Can substitute cheddar, mozzarella, co-jack, pepper jack or one of your own favorites). 11 Serve plain or with dipping sauces such as spaghetti, pizza, marinara, ranch or bbq.';
