REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3472', `RecipeID`='3472', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Line a plate with parchment paper and sprinkle the shredded Parmesan on top, spread it out evenly Microwave circles of shredded Parmesan cheese until they’re golden brown. (about 2 minutes) Then CAREFULLY place the circles on upside down bowls; let them harden. NOTES  When the Parm is resting on the bowl, place a sheet of parchment paper on top of the cheese, and place another bowl on top of the Parchment paper to help form the bowl. a tall GLASS also works well if you want a deeper bowl. If the bowl breaks dont worry, they still make great toppings!';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3473', `RecipeID`='3473', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. 2 Line the baking sheet with the silpat (preferred) or parchment. 3 Place a heaping tablespoon of Parmesan on the lined baking sheet and lightly pat it down to make about a 2-inch circle. 4 Repeat with the remaining Parmesan, placing the spoonfuls about 1 inch apart. 5 Bake at 400 degrees F for 3 to 5 minutes until golden and crisp. 6 Allow to cool on the baking sheet before removing carefully with a spatula for serving.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3474', `RecipeID`='3474', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Slice apples about 1/2 thick. Spread one slice with peanut butter, then top with granola and chocolate chips. Top with second apple slice. Great with a glass of milk :)';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3475', `RecipeID`='3475', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='line a square pan 15 by 10 by 2 with wax paper. both sides spread cereal in pan over medium heat, bring corn syrup and sugar to boil, remove from heat add peanut butter mix until well blended pour over cereal cool in fridge for 5-10 minutes/until chilled break into pieces or for nice and easy presentation cut into bars store in plastic bag refrigerated or not really doesnt matter add-ins: chocolate chips, nuts of any sort or whatever u want :) enjoy';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3476', `RecipeID`='3476', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='Mix sugar and syrup together, bring to a boil. Boil 1 to 1 1/2 minutes (or you can count to 100). Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, stir. Add cereal and coconut. Drop on waxed paper.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3477', `RecipeID`='3477', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1 Brush the cut side of the peach with oil and grill over medium coals, cut side down until grill marks develop, about 3 to 5 minutes. 2 Remove from grill. 3 Place on a plate with slices of prosciutto and grilled bread.';
REPLACE INTO `Directions` SET `ID`='3478', `RecipeID`='3478', `SortOrder`='0', `Directions`='1.Leaving the peel on the bananas, slice each in half lengthwise. Smear the inside with peanut butter, and sprinkle with chocolate chips. Place the two halves back together and wrap each banana individually in aluminum foil. 2.Cook in the hot coals of a campfire until the banana is hot, and the chocolate has melted, about 10 to 15 minutes, depending on the heat of the coals.';
